{"key":"processedPost-13724086","value":{"id":13724086,"first":13718994,"last":13724468,"when":1294074022,"utime":"01/03/11 07:00 PM","cleanedPost":"Spraying Lysol into the air is a waste of product.&nbsp; Lysol is a <i>surface</i> disinfectant.&nbsp; Oust is an aerial disinfectant, or you can mix up a ten percent bleach solution and spray that into the air.&nbsp; As the water/bleach droplets settle, they will 'grab' contaminant spores and carry them to the floor.&nbsp; According to my particulate counter, spraying the air with plain water is just as effective as having bleach in it, but I use bleach in the hopes it will help to nuke some of those as they travel to the floor.<br />Clean glove/still air box with soap and water.&nbsp; Flame sterilize needles or other tools which come in contact with sterile media.<br />RR"}}